Done. `/private/tmp/findpicked-games/blockdrop/index.html` is ready. Summary:

**Gameplay**
- 10×20 grid, all 7 pieces (I, O, T, S, Z, J, L) with 4 rotations and simple wall kicks
- 7-bag randomizer, ghost piece, next-piece preview
- Soft drop (+1/cell), hard drop (+2/cell), line-clear scoring (100/300/500/800 × level)
- Level up every 10 lines, speed ramps from 1000ms to 100ms
- Best score persisted to localStorage

**Design**
- Apple-minimal: `#fafafa` bg, `#1d1d1f` text, `#0071e3` accent, -apple-system stack
- White cards with soft shadows, pill buttons (44px height, 22px radius)
- Soft iOS-hue block palette, rounded 18% corners, subtle highlight
- Faint grid lines, frosted-glass overlay (`backdrop-filter`) for start / pause / game over
- Top-left minimal `←` back link to `../`; all UI in English; no "Tetris" anywhere

**Controls**
- Keyboard: ←/→ move, ↑ rotate, Z reverse-rotate, ↓ soft drop, Space hard drop, P pause
- Touch: on-screen pad (appears ≤720px) with hold-to-repeat for move/soft drop, plus swipe/tap on the board (tap rotate, drag to move, quick down-swipe hard drop)
- Responsive canvas sizing adapts cell size to viewport
